#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _versions/main/guides/deploying-to-openshift-docker-howto.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Deploying Quarkus Java applications to OpenShift by using a Docker build strategy"
msgstr "使用 Docker 构建策略将 Quarkus Java 应用程序部署到 OpenShift"

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/deploying-to-openshift-docker-howto.adoc
msgid "As an application developer, you can deploy your applications to {openshift-long} by using the Docker build strategy as a deployment option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/deploying-to-openshift-docker-howto.adoc
msgid ""
"This strategy builds the artifacts outside the {openshift} cluster, either locally or in a CI environment, and provides them to the {openshift} build system together with a Dockerfile.\n"
"The artifacts include JAR files or a native executable.\n"
"The {openshift} cluster builds the container image and provides it as an image stream."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/deploying-to-openshift-docker-howto.adoc
msgid ""
"This functionality is provided by the `quarkus-openshift` extension.\n"
"If you want to use a custom Dockerfile, add the file to the `src/main/docker` directory or another location inside the module.\n"
"Set the path to your Dockerfile with the `quarkus.openshift.jvm-dockerfile` property."
msgstr ""

